Hello folks, my 2nd annotation of a fun game with an aggressive white.  Your comments will be read and appreciated.

My standard opening move.
a surprise play from black.  white isn't sure of black's intent...
white passes the pawn, white's thinking of controlling the center.

white offers to swap knights.  white's goal here to maintain center and ensure pawn(s) in the e file to keep a defendable defender in front of the king.

white was thinking here something along the line of: 8. ... g6 9. Nxg6 hxg6 10. Qxg6+ Kd7 11. cxd5 exd5 12. Qg4+ Ke8 13. Qxd4 Rh4 14. f4 but...

a surprise, black moves king.  white thought Bg5+ to skewer queen, but then white saw if Bg5+ then 9...Nf6 and black would be safe for the moment... then white saw and played the better Bb4+.  white has a few conditional moves set here.
this might be the most interesting # of my gameknot.com time.  Thank you gameknot and thank you community!  Cheers all.
